⁣Are you sticking with your 2023 fitness goals?😅💪🏼⠀
⠀
Reminder : Just because it’s a new year, doesn’t mean anything will change… unless YOU are putting in the work! ⠀
It all comes down to CONSISTENCY and DISCIPLINE! 
⠀
Only about 16% of people follow through with their New Year’s resolutions ….. that’s crazy!!🤯 ⠀
⠀
🔅Don’t just write out “resolutions” once a year… set a VISION for the year… ⠀
🔅Break that down into monthly goals⠀

⠀
YOU GOT THIS!!! 💯

⁣A NEW WEEK to STAY CONSISTENT with your goals💯 ⠀

⠀
Monthly, weekly, (I write mine on Sundays).. whatever works for you!!⠀
Forget the “yearly resolutions” and stick with the small action steps in achieving your weekly goals! ⠀
⠀
A few of my goals this week:⠀
⠀
✨ Drink a gallon of water a day (why is this so hard 😅)⠀
✨ Limit social media time If it’s not work related⠀
✨ Devotions before bed (instead of phone)⠀
✨ Fasted Cardio every morning (I’m on a prep)⠀

⁣⁣TRUST the process…Your time is coming 💥
⠀
When you are giving it your ALL… the results will show… the opportunities will come! ⠀🙏🏼
⠀
I didn’t wake up one day and have Abs.. ⠀
I didn’t get my magazine cover, runway shows and modeling/commercial opportunities by sitting on the couch watching Netflix..⠀
I didn’t get my dream apartment in Miami by someone paying my bills..⠀
⠀
Naw.. it’s called hard work and discipline!!💯
It’s cutting out ALL distractions (and people that serve no purpose) and focusing on my goals!⠀
It’s waking up early, & training even when I don’t feel like it.⠀
It’s working in overtime … 24/7.. being a go-getter entrepreneur and not giving up when I get a “No” for an answer. ⠀

It’s believing in myself, having CONFIDENCE in my value and what I bring to the table.. ⠀
and working my way to the top, not by luck, but by determination, discipline and consistency!!

❌You don’t need a fan club to achieve your goals..⠀
Don’t wait around for others.. Be your OWN motivation and get to work!!❌
⠀
There’s nothing in this world you CAN’T do, so stop doubting yourself.. and start working harder. Period. ⠀

God is moving in Cuba 🇨🇺 

What a blessing it is to pour into others 🙏🏼♥️

This mission trip was so humbling for me. It’s incredible to see God’s work even amongst a poor communist country.  Even though they’re struggling with poverty, they still find a way to worship & give praise! 🥹

What a huge wake-up call … we take SO much for granted in the US! 

While I was there, I had the opportunity to speak six times to different groups of youth, women, and children, bringing them positivity and hope. 
 I shared my testimony and talked about identity, self worth, loneliness, depression, suicide, insecurities and pain. 

I witnessed God speaking through me straight to their hearts. Tears welled up in the eyes of numerous women, seemingly releasing the burdens of their past traumas, and I prayed over young teenagers seeking transformation in their life. 

I also taught dance routines and workouts! 
Even amid extremely hot conditions without air conditioning, this filled my heart with joy every day! ☺️ 💃 

The gratification of selflessness and the fulfillment found in giving without expecting personal gain is so rewarding!! 
I’ll be back again soon 🇨🇺
